<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="299" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d299">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/415: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-16T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>172. Department’s instruction No. 684, December 8, 1921,<note n="1" xml:id="d299fn1">Not printed.</note> and your telegram No. 3,
                            January 6, 1922, 2 P.M. Pending further instructions do not request
                            renewal of preferences for 1923.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
